
Signal Aggregation Engine (SIG)
1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the canonical data contracts and field-level definitions for the Signal Aggregation Engine (SIG).
It complements NS-SIG-007 — DATAMODEL by:
providing semantic definitions for every field
specifying invariants and constraints
clarifying cross-engine expectations
acting as the definitive reference for consumers (PIE, SIM, DAT, FLO, DRE, GGP)
2. Data Definition Principles
Semantic Stability — field meanings never change
Immutability by Default — authoritative records are append-only
Explainability — scores and decisions must be interpretable
Minimalism — only essential data is exposed downstream
ID-First Contracts — cross-engine references use IDs, not payload copying
3. Canonical Signal Contract
3.1 signal
Represents an atomic observation.
Field
Type
Definition
signal_id
UUID
Globally unique identifier for the signal
signal_type
String
Canonical signal name (taxonomy-defined)
signal_class
Enum
market, demand, supply, execution, financial, system
source_system
String
Originating system identifier
observed_at
Timestamp (UTC)
When the observation occurred externally
received_at
Timestamp (UTC)
When SIG ingested the signal
value
JSON
Normalized observation payload
unit
String
Unit of measure (if applicable)
trust_score
Decimal (0–1)
Reliability of the source and integrity
confidence_score
Decimal (0–1)
Completeness and measurement quality
decay_model
String
Name of decay function
decay_params
JSON
Parameters (half-life, TTL)
normalization_ruleset
String
Normalization ruleset name
normalization_version
String
Normalization ruleset version
scoring_ruleset
String
Scoring ruleset name
scoring_version
String
Scoring ruleset version
dedupe_ruleset
String
Deduplication ruleset name
dedupe_version
String
Deduplication ruleset version
correlation_hints
JSON
Optional correlation metadata
created_at
Timestamp (UTC)
Persistence time
Invariants:
signal_id is immutable
value meaning never changes
scores are explicit, never inferred
4. Raw Capture Contract
4.1 signal_raw_capture
Preserves raw inputs for replay and audit.
Field
Type
Definition
capture_id
UUID
Raw capture identifier
source_system
String
Source name
raw_ref
String
Upstream artifact or event ID
payload_hash
String
Hash of raw payload
received_at
Timestamp
Ingestion time
5. Provenance Contract
5.1 signal_provenance
Links signals to upstream sources.
Field
Type
Definition
signal_id
UUID
Canonical signal
source_type
Enum
mux, telemetry, vendor
source_ref
String
artifact_id or event_id
6. Deduplication Contract
6.1 signal_dedupe_ref
Represents duplicate linkage.
Field
Type
Definition
dedupe_id
UUID
Deduplication reference
signal_id
UUID
Canonical signal
dedupe_key
String
Stable dedupe key
linked_at
Timestamp
Link time
7. Decision Artifact Contract
7.1 signal_decision
Captures all SIG decisions.
Field
Type
Definition
decision_id
UUID
Decision identifier
decision_type
String
admit, normalize, score, dedupe, control
subject_ref
String
signal_id, source, or job
outcome
String
Decision result
rationale
JSON
Structured explanation
ruleset_name
String
Ruleset applied
ruleset_version
String
Ruleset version
evaluated_at
Timestamp
Decision time
correlation_id
UUID
Traceability ID
